= Importance of Tawḥīd and its virtues

== Tawḥīd is the Greatest Pillar of Islām

It is the greatest foundation of Islam, and one cannot become Muslim without
bearing witness to the oneness of Allāh and acknowledging His exclusive right to
be worshipped, while denying any worship to others besides Him.

The Prophet #pbuh said,

#hadith-block[
  بُنِيَ الإِسْلَامُ عَلَى خَمْسٍ: شَهَادَةِ أَنْ لَا إِلهَ إِلَّا اللهُ وَأَنَّ
  مُحَمَّدًا رَسُولُ اللهِ ، وَإِقَامِ الصَّلَاةِ ، وَإِيتَاءِ الزَّكَاةِ ،
  وَالحَجِّ ، وَصَوْمِ رَمَضَانَ.
][
  “Islam is built on five (cornerstones):

  - The testimony that there is no God worthy of worship except Allāh, and Muḥammad
    #pbuh is the Messenger of Allāh.
  - Establishing prayer.
  - Giving _zakāh_ (obligatory charity).
  - Fasting in Ramadan.
  - Performing the Hajj to the house (Kaʿbah).”@bukhari[vol. 1, pp. 150--1, \#8]
    [Agreed upon]#footnote[This means that both Imam al-Bukhārī and Imam Muslim
      have narrated the same _ḥadīth_ in their _Ṣaḥīḥ_ collections.]
]


== Tawḥīd is the most important duty and the first obligation

It takes precedence over all actions and is the foremost of all significant
duties because of its high status and paramount importance. It is the first
thing one is called to. The Prophet #pbuh said to Muʿādh #pleasedHIM when he
sent him to Yemen,

#hadith-block[
  إِنَّكَ تَأْتِي قَوْمًا مِنْ أَهْلِ الْكِتَابِ ، فَلْيَكُنْ أَوَّلَ مَا
  تَدْعُوهُمْ إِلَيْهِ شَهَادَةُ أَنْ لَا إِلٰهَ إِلَّا اللَّهُ - وَفِي رِوَايَةٍ:
  إِلَى أَنْ يُوَحِّدُوا اللَّهَ.
][
  “You are going to a people from the People of the Book. Call them to testify
  that there is no God worthy of worship except Allāh.” In another narration, he
  said, “Call them to the oneness of Allāh.” (Agreed upon)@muslim[vol. 1, p. 371,
  \#11]
]

== Worship is not accepted except with Tawḥīd

Tawḥīd is a condition for the validity of worship and the foundation of its
acceptance. Worship is not called worship unless it is accompanied by Tawḥīd,
just as prayer is not called prayer unless it is accompanied by _wuḍūʾ_
(ablution). If Shirk (associating partners with Allāh) accompanies worship, it
corrupts it -- just as impurity nullifies purification. Worship without Tawḥīd
becomes an act of Shirk that invalidates deeds, renders them worthless, and
condemns the person to eternal punishment in Hell.


== Tawḥīd is the Key to Security and Guidance in This Life and the Hereafter

The evidence for it is in the words of Allāh,

#quran-block[
  ٱلَّذِينَ ءَامَنُواْ وَلَمۡ يَلۡبِسُوٓاْ إِيمَٰنَهُم بِظُلۡمٍ أُوْلَٰٓئِكَ لَهُمُ ٱلۡأَمۡنُ وَهُم مُّهۡتَدُونَ ٨٢
][
  Those who believe and do not mix their faith with wrongdoing -- for them there
  is security, and they are rightly guided. (Al-Anʿām, Q6:82)
]

The “wrongdoing” mentioned here refers to Shirk, as clarified by the Prophet
#pbuh.

Ibn Kathīr #mercyHIM explained, “Those who worship Allāh alone with sincerity
and do not associate anything with Him -- they are the ones who will have
security on the Day of Judgment and guidance in both this life and the
Hereafter.”[ADD REFERENCE]

Whoever perfects Tawḥīd will attain complete security and guidance and will
enter Paradise without suffering punishment.

Shirk is the gravest injustice, while Tawḥīd is the highest form of justice.

== Tawḥīd is the Path to Paradise and Salvation from Hell

The Prophet #pbuh said,

#hadith-block[
  مَنْ شَهِدَ أَنْ لا إِلٰهَ إِلَّا اللهُ وَحْدَهُ لا شَرِيكَ لَهُ ، وَأَنَّ
  مُحَمَّدًا عَبْدُهُ وَرَسُولُهُ ، وَأَنَّ عِيسَى عَبْدُ اللهِ وَابْنُ أَمَتِهِ ،
  وَكَلِمَتُهُ أَلْقَاهَا إِلَىٰ مَرْيَمَ ، وَرُوحٌ مِنْهُ ، وَالْجَنَّةَ حَقٌّ ،
  وَالنَّارَ حَقٌّ ،أَدْخَلَهُ مِنْ أَبْوَابِ الْجَنَّةِ الثَّمَانِيَةِ أَيِّهَا
  شَاءَ.
][
  “Whoever testifies that there is no God worthy of being worshipped except Allāh
  alone, with no partner, that Muḥammad #pbuh is His servant and messenger, that
  Jesus #salamHIM is the servant of Allāh and the son of His female slave, and His
  word that He bestowed upon Mary, and a spirit from Him, and that Paradise is
  real and Hell is real, Allāh will admit him into Paradise through any of its
  eight gates he wishes.” (Agreed upon)@muslim[vol. 1, p. 381, \#20]
]

He #pbuh also said,

#hadith-block[
  فَإِنَّ اللهَ قَدْ حَرَّمَ عَلَى النَّارِ مَنْ قَالَ: لَا إِلٰهَ إِلَّا اللهُ، يَبْتَغِي بِذَلِكَ وَجْهَ اللهِ.
][
  “Indeed, Allāh has forbidden Hell for anyone who says, ‘There is no God worthy
  of being worshipped except Allāh,’ sincerely seeking the pleasure of Allāh.” (Agreed
  upon)@bukhari[vol. 1, pp. 391--2, \#429]
]

== Tawḥīd Is Salvation from the Hardships of This World and the Hereafter

Ibn al-Qayyim #mercyHIM said, “Tawḥīd is the refuge of both its enemies and its
allies.” [ADD REFERENCE?]

For its enemies, Tawḥīd saves them from the hardships and difficulties of this
world, as Allāh says,

#quran-block[
  فَإِذَا رَكِبُواْ فِي ٱلۡفُلۡكِ دَعَوُاْ ٱللَّهَ مُخۡلِصِينَ لَهُ ٱلدِّينَ فَلَمَّا نَجَّىٰهُمۡ إِلَى ٱلۡبَرِّ إِذَا هُمۡ يُشۡرِكُونَ ٦٥
][
  When they embark on a ship, they call upon Allāh, sincere in their faith in Him
  alone. But when He delivers them safely to land, they associate others with
  Him. (Al-ʿAnkabūt Q29:65)
]

For its allies, Tawḥīd saves them from the hardships of both this world and the
Hereafter. This is the way of Allāh with His servants. There is nothing more
powerful in repelling the trials of this world than Tawḥīd.

That is why the supplication of distress is based on Tawḥīd, just as the prayer
of Prophet Yunus #salamHIM was -- no one ever called upon Allāh with it while in
distress except that Allāh relieved their hardship through Tawḥīd.#footnote[The
supplication of Yunus Peace be upon him is mentioned in Q21:87, «There is no
Deity except You; exalted are You. Indeed, I have been of the wrongdoers.»]

Thus, nothing throws people into severe hardship more than Shirk (associating
partners with Allāh), and nothing rescues them from it except Tawḥīd. It is the
ultimate refuge, shelter, and protection for all of creation.

== Tawḥīd Is the Wisdom Behind the Creation of Humans and Jinn

Allāh says,

#quran-block[
  وَمَا خَلَقۡتُ ٱلۡجِنَّ وَٱلۡإِنسَ إِلَّا لِيَعۡبُدُونِ ٥٦
][
  “I did not create the Jinn and humans except to worship Me.” (Al-Dhāriyāt,
  Q51:56)
]

*Meaning:* to establish Tawḥīd, to single out Allāh in all aspects of worship.

The Messengers #salamTHEM were sent, the Scriptures were revealed, Laws were
established, and creation itself was brought into existence for the sole purpose
of worshipping Allāh alone, without associating anything with Him.